# Pem — Product Pivot: Thought Organizer

## Dev environment — no legacy support

This is pre-production. Nothing is live. No users. No data to preserve.
Delete everything that belonged to the old prep architecture without hesitation.
No migration shims. No backwards compatibility. No feature flags wrapping old behavior.
If it says "prep" and it is not the dump input — delete it.

When **this pivot** (product, schema, routes, or UX) changes, update **this file** and any other **`.mdc`** / **`README.md`** sections that describe the same facts — see **`pem-project.mdc`** (*Keeping `.cursor/rules` in sync*).

---

## What Pem is now

The problem: thoughts living rent-free in your head. The mental load that surfaces
while driving, in bed, between meetings, in the middle of something else. You cannot
act on them right now but you cannot stop carrying them either.

The solution: dump your thoughts. Pem organizes them.

Pem is not a todo app. Pem is not a productivity tool. Pem is not a prep engine.
Pem is a mind-clearing tool. The primary feeling is relief — not productivity.

**The loop:**

```
User dumps (voice or text, anytime, messy, no structure required)
  → Pem extracts actionable items
  → Pem classifies, batches, sequences, and tones each item
  → Items land in the inbox — organized and prioritized
  → User reads what Pem figured out
  → User taps to go deeper or act
  → Head is clear
```

The inbox is the output. Pem fills it. The user never "creates tasks."
Items arrive like emails — something was figured out and sent to you.

