## The pipeline (replaces the prep pipeline)

```
POST /dumps (text)
  → save dump row (raw text on `dumps.text`)
  → enqueue extraction job
  → return { dumpId } immediately

Extraction worker (BullMQ):
  → classify and extract actionable items from dump text
  → for each actionable item:
      - determine tone (confident | tentative | idea | someday)
      - determine urgency (today | this_week | someday | none)
      - detect exact datetime OR period
      - detect batch_key if batchable
  → insert actionable rows
  → SSE push to client: inbox.updated

GET /inbox
  → today's view: actionables where status=inbox, urgency=today
  → ordered: overdue first, then by due_at asc, then quick wins

GET /inbox/all
  → full list: this_week + batches + someday + dismissed
  → grouped by batch_key where applicable
```

No calendar merging in iteration 1. Calendar is a future feature.

